<body>
<div class="strip"><i class="e"></i><i class="w"></i><i class="d"></i><i class="k"></i></div>
<div class="grid"></div>

<nav><div class="wrap">
  <div class="logo">🚦 ANDON<span class="dim"> /行灯</span></div>
  <div class="navlinks">
    <a href="#how">How it works</a>
    <a href="#anywhere">Board from anywhere</a>
    <a class="star" href="https://github.com/tianshanghong/agent-andon">★ Star on GitHub</a>
  </div>
</div></nav>

<header class="wrap hero">
  <div>
    <div class="kicker rise" style="animation-delay:.02s">Open source · zero dependencies · <b>self-hosted</b></div>
    <h1 class="rise" style="animation-delay:.08s">Your AI coding agents,<br><b>at a glance.</b></h1>
    <p class="lede rise" style="animation-delay:.16s">A status board &amp; alerts for <b>Claude Code</b> and <b>Codex</b>. Run several at once — the board lights up the instant one is <b>working, needs you, done,</b> or <b>stuck</b>. No babysitting the terminal.</p>

    <div class="kicker rise" style="animation-delay:.20s;margin-top:32px;color:var(--done)">⚡ Zero setup — three commands, straight onto our relay</div>
    <div class="cmd rise" style="animation-delay:.24s">
      <button id="copy" aria-label="Copy commands">COPY</button>
      <code id="cmd"><span class="p">$</span> npm i -g agent-andon
<span class="p">$</span> andon hosted setup https://relay.agentandon.com
<span class="p">$</span> andon install claude</code>
    </div>
    <div class="hint rise" style="animation-delay:.28s">install the CLI · pair with our relay · wire your agent — then restart your session and open the board on your phone. Just trying it out? <code style="font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--muted)">npx agent-andon serve --demo</code></div>

    <div class="cta rise" style="animation-delay:.34s">
      <a class="btn primary" href="#anywhere">Phone push from anywhere <span class="tag">managed</span></a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="https://github.com/tianshanghong/agent-andon">★ Star on GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="board" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="card e pulse rise" style="animation-delay:.30s"><div class="st">✕ Stuck</div><div class="nm">data-pipeline</div><div class="msg">tests failing — needs a look</div></div>
    <div class="card w pulse rise" style="animation-delay:.40s"><div class="st">! Needs you</div><div class="nm">ledger-api</div><div class="msg">approve: Bash(git push)</div></div>
    <div class="card d rise" style="animation-delay:.50s"><div class="st">✓ Ready</div><div class="nm">payments-svc</div><div class="msg">turn handed back</div></div>
    <div class="card k rise" style="animation-delay:.60s"><div class="st">↻ Working</div><div class="nm">checkout-api</div><div class="msg">running · 2 background</div></div>
  </div>
</header>

<section id="how" class="wrap">
  <div class="eyebrow">How it works</div>
  <h2>Hook → tiny server → the board.</h2>
  <p class="sec-lede">Each tool's <b style="color:var(--text)">native hook</b> reports state changes — no change to your workflow. A small HTTP server on your computer relays them; any screen holds a live stream and shows the change in well under a second.</p>
  <div class="steps">
    <div class="step"><div class="n">01 · detect</div><h3>Native hooks</h3><p>Claude Code &amp; Codex fire lifecycle hooks. <code style="font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--text)">andon install claude</code> wires them for you (with a backup).</p></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="n">02 · relay</div><h3>Your computer</h3><p>A zero-dependency Node server receives the events. macOS · Linux · Windows. Nothing leaves your machine.</p></div>
    <div class="step"><div class="n">03 · display</div><h3>Any screen</h3><p>iPad, phone, or browser — a signal bar across the top is the tower light; the most-urgent row floats up and pulses.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="anywhere" class="wrap">
  <div class="band">
    <div class="eyebrow">Board from anywhere</div>
    <h2>Phone push, your way.</h2>
    <p class="sec-lede">Local-first and free to self-host forever. To reach the board — and get push — from anywhere, route through a relay that's <b style="color:var(--text)">content-blind</b>: it stores only ciphertext it can't decrypt, so it never sees your prompts, code, or messages.</p>
    <div class="opts">
      <div class="opt managed">
        <div class="h">☁️ Managed relay <span class="badge">live</span></div>
        <h3>The easy way — no server</h3>
        <p>Zero setup, no Tailscale, no HTTPS to configure. Opt in and get phone push from anywhere.</p>
        <code>$ andon hosted setup https://relay.agentandon.com</code>
      </div>
      <div class="opt self">
        <div class="h">⌘ Self-host</div>
        <h3>Run your own relay</h3>
        <p>Same open-source code. Or expose the local board to just your devices with Tailscale.</p>
        <code>$ andon relay   ·   andon verify &lt;url&gt;</code>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="priv">🔒&nbsp;<span><b>Verifiable, not just trusted.</b> Your status content is end-to-end encrypted and the relay's code is reproducible from source — <code style="font-family:var(--mono);color:var(--text)">andon verify</code> confirms it serves the exact open-source code.</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<footer>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div>
      <div class="lg">🚦 AGENT ANDON</div>
      <div class="fine">Open source under AGPL-3.0 · © 2026 wwang<br>"Andon" (行灯) — the factory signal light that tells the floor, at a glance, whether a line is running or needs a human.</div>
    </div>
